---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 128
By: Sri Ramakrishna
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Sacrifice and Suffering=Contemptus Mundi
---
The seeds of Vajrabantul do not fall to the bottom of the tree. They are
carried by the wind far off and take root there. So the spirit of a prophet
manifests itself at a distance and he is appreciated there.
